<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dizy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok ok- I am not yet of age to go to the planes- but at 30 am venturing into more dungeons. My question is about the looting order I have heard of in different areas.(planes mostly- but some dungeons as well)Is it true thatyou must have been in the dungeon/plane X mount of times before you can even be in the random for an item? If so- why is  this? My thought is, I worked as hard as the rest and should be eligible to random as much as anyone else. Elightenment appreicated.<BR>Thanks  ~~ Diz</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dizy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm lots a help here....  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">taobob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If it was immediate help you were looking for, I'd check with the main EQ message board it is much more active than the cozy little place Muse has going here. This discussion board usually has daily visitors not lurkers like the main boards....<P>As far as I know Plane loot goes according to a groups loot order (which is ofttimes random) and that there are usually waiting lists for groups to actually combat the NPC that drops 'k3wl l00t'.. I suppose this depends on the loot you were looking for and when you are visiting the dungeons...<P>I too am to young to have found out for myself and with any luck by the time I get there everyone will have moved to Velious...<BR><P>------------------<BR>Blackivar the Cunning<BR>Halfling Rogue<BR>17th Season<BR>Druzzil Ro Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Inky Caster</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Planes loot is usually done 1 of 2 ways in my experiences with those hellish places.<BR>1 If you are with a guild, then they will often award items to those members of the guild that they feel have contributed to the raid in a great way<BR>2 It is randomed off between everyone who can use that item because many things are class specific and no drop<BR>That is how it has been in my experiences in plane raids. feel free to flame me if you feel I am totally incorrect.<P>------------------<BR>Blood is like honey... thick and sweet.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Delthanor Silverthorn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The latter way you mention is what I've seen.  I've only been on two planes raids so far, but this is how they went for armor drops:<BR>(Multiple guilds, btw)<P>Creature dies and drops an item usable only by class X. <P>If it completes a full set of planar armor for someone, they get it and are no longer in rotation for that type of armor.  Usually they have to be wearing the full set to prove their need.<P>If it is a chest-piece, all roll who don't own it already.<P>If it is another piece, all who have not won any of that class type of armor rolls.   When all have won a piece, all of class X are eligible again.<P>Anyone can pass on an item, if they don't want it.  (To avoid taking drek pieces and then being ineligible later.)  If everyone eligible for rolling passes, ALL of class X rolls and the winner gets the item, but it does not count as a loot, and does not affect their eligibility to roll on subsequent items.<P>Loot masters will call out the rolls.  Most raids continue pulling even while determining loot winners.  Sometimes a second piece drops before the first piece is rolled on.  PAY ATTENTION to what roll is called.  If a drek roll happens, and a good piece has also fallen, don't expect to get the good piece if you win the drek roll.  You get the drek, and then must roll again for the good piece.<P>Here's the big rule for raids:<BR>The raid is not for YOU, it is for everyone.  When a piece of class armor drops, and you don't win the roll, be happy for the winner.  Your turn will eventually come.  There is no way you would get anything without the support of the full raid, so cheer all winners, and enjoy the raid.  I've found some of the most intense and fun times in EQ on these raids.  </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
